# OSINT Tools and Resources for Financial Investigations (Expanded)

A categorized, non-exhaustive list of open-source intelligence tools, databases, and platforms used in fraud investigation, vendor screening, and financial crime research.

## Corporate Records & Business Registries

- OpenCorporates
- Companies House (UK)
- SEC EDGAR
- FINRA BrokerCheck
- IRS Tax Exempt Org Search
- Secretary of State Business Search
- Department of State – Corporation & Business Entity Database
- Bizapedia
- CorporationWiki
- Glassdoor
- Better Business Bureau (BBB)
- Yelp (for ghost companies)

## Domain, Network & Infrastructure Intelligence

- WHOIS (who.is / ICANN Lookup)
- SecurityTrails
- ViewDNS.info
- DNSdumpster
- Shodan
- GreyNoise
- Censys
- Robtex
- MXToolbox
- BuiltWith
- Netcraft
- ZoomEye (China-hosted)

## Legal, Civil, & Criminal Records

- PACER (US Federal Court System)
- CourtListener
- RECAP Archive
- Justia
- Trellis Law (State Court Dockets)
- Local/State Judiciary Portals (varies by county/state)
- Nationwide Inmate Locator (BOP.gov)
- Vinelink (Victim notification & offender search)
- OffenderData.com

## Political & Regulatory Disclosures

- OpenSecrets
- FEC.gov (Campaign Contributions)
- FARA.gov (Foreign Agent Registrations)
- USAspending.gov
- FinCEN Beneficial Ownership Database (2024+)
- SEC Form ADV (Investment Advisor Disclosures)
- LobbyView (Harvard)
- LittleSis.org
- InfluenceWatch.org

## Sanctions, PEPs & Watchlists

- OFAC Sanctions List (SDN)
- UN Consolidated Sanctions List
- EU Sanctions Map
- Interpol Red Notices
- FBI Most Wanted
- CIA World Leaders List
- HM Treasury Sanctions List (UK)
- ROSTEKHNADZOR (Russia Sanctions, RU)
- SECO (Switzerland)
- AML-CFT.eu Sanctions Aggregator
- World-Check (commercial, Refinitiv)
- Factiva (PEP alerts, commercial)

## International & Offshore Entities

- OCCRP Aleph
- ICIJ Offshore Leaks Database
- Panama Papers
- Paradise Papers
- Global Open Data Index
- Global Legal Entity Identifier (GLEIF)
- Orbis (Bureau van Dijk, commercial)
- BvD Zephyr (M&A database)
- Swissleaks

## People & Identity Tracing

- LinkedIn
- Pipl
- That’sThem
- Spokeo
- TruePeopleSearch
- FastPeopleSearch
- Radaris
- WhitePages
- BeenVerified
- PeekYou
- NumLookup (phone # metadata)
- AnyWho (US)
- ZoomInfo (commercial contact profiles)

## Property, GIS, and Asset Tracing

- County Assessor GIS Portals (varies by county)
- Netronline (gateway to US assessor and recorder sites)
- ACRIS (NYC property database)
- ParcelQuest (California)
- Sanborn Maps / Historic Plat Maps
- LandWatch (for rural/undeclared land assets)

## Document & Metadata Analysis

- InVID (video verification)
- Metadata2Go
- ExifTool
- PDF Examiner
- OSINT Combine PDF Scanner
- FOCA (Metadata & document recon)

## Social, Behavioral, & Web Presence

- Google Dorking / Advanced Operators
- X-Ray Search (LinkedIn, Facebook, etc.)
- Archive.org (Wayback Machine)
- CachedView
- Hunchly (web capture & evidence)
- Hunter.io (email discovery)
- MailTester.com
- HaveIBeenPwned
- Pastebin (leaked info)
- GhostProject.fr

## Email, IP, & Credential Checks

- EmailRep.io
- EmailHippo
- MXToolbox
- IPInfo.io
- AbuseIPDB
- LeakCheck.io
- IntelligenceX

## Image & Facial Analysis

- TinEye (reverse image search)
- Google Lens
- Yandex Images
- ExifTool (EXIF metadata)
- FotoForensics
- PimEyes (facial recognition, paid)
- Social Searcher (username/content analysis)

## Automation & Recon Frameworks

- Maltego (graph-based link analysis)
- SpiderFoot
- Recon-ng
- Metagoofil
- Osmedeus
- TheHarvester
- Nmap (network recon, deeper layer)

## General OSINT Aggregators / Toolkits

- OSINT Framework (https://osintframework.com/)
- Bellingcat's Online Investigation Toolkit
- IntelTechniques by Michael Bazzell
- Awesome-OSINT (GitHub curated list)
- Open Source Intelligence Tools and Resources Handbook (Michael Bazzell)


